The Wildcats of St. Trinian's is the fifth
British
comedy film set in the fictional
St Trinian's School
, released in
1980
.
It poked fun at the
British trade union movement which had been responsible for the recent wave of strikes that culminated in the
Winter of Discontent
.
The film was not a critical success and unlike the previous four films in the series, has yet to be released on
DVD .
Plot
After deciding that they're asked to do too much work, the pupils at St. Trinian's school form a trade union and go on strike.
